title: Volcanic Eruptions, US Counties, 1960- 2007
name: Volcanic Eruptions, US Counties, 1960- 2007
description:
SHELDUS is a county-level data set for the U.S. on 18 different natural hazard event types along with property and crop losses, injuries, and fatalities for the period January 1960 through December 2007. The database was compiled to examine spatial and temporal variability in historical hazard events and associated losses. U.S. county boundaries are adjusted to 2000 designations.  Event and Loss Data Sources: The data were derived from several existing national data sources, of which National Climatic Data Center's monthly Storm Data publications are the major data source.

Data in this map represent sums of different information, such as number of hazards that occurred in a particular county along with number of injuries, and do not show specific hazards and subsequent information regarding that particular hazard.

author.source: SHELDUS, Spatial Hazards Events and Losses Database for the United States
